concludeQuestions.improve: Testing more than one dune, taking more samples in each chosen location, and more locations along the sampled dune would increase confidence.

consistent-reason.value: The minimum amount of samples needed to make a trend is three to rule out errors or flukes. I used the minimum for efficiency since I estimated I would have about ten points sampled, though the more samples, the better the accuracy.

evenly-space-reason.value: Roughly even spacing means fewer variables in the experiment, so the easier it is to test the hypothesis.
